Redi/Gent and McWilliams parameterization¶

gmredi package¶

Redi/GM parameterization represents the effect of geostrophic eddies

$\,$
$\,$
$$ u^{*}=\begin{pmatrix}u^{*}\\v^{*}\\w^{*}\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}-\partial_{z}(\kappa_{GM}S_{x})\\-\partial_{z}(\kappa_{GM}S_{y})\\\partial_{x}(\kappa_{GM}S_{x})+\partial_{y}(\kappa_{GM}S_{y})\end{pmatrix} $$

$$ \kappa_{GM}: \mathrm{GM\,\,coeffcicient} $$$$ S_{x}=-\frac{\partial_{x}\sigma}{\partial_{z}\sigma} $$$$ S_{y}=-\frac{\partial_{y}\sigma}{\partial_{z}\sigma} $$

Calculation¶

Mixed Layer depth from T and S¶

  • Compute σ$_{0}$ from temperature and salinity 3D fields: σ(T,S,P=0)
  • Compute σ$_{0}$(θ$_{0}$ - 0.8°C, S$_{0}$, P=0) with θ$_{0}$ and S$_{0}$ the surface values
  • Find the depth where σ$_{0}$(θ, S, P$_{0}$) - σ0(θ$_{0}$-0.8°C, S$_{0}$, P$_{0}$) is minimized

ACC transport¶

The Antarctic Circumpolar Current transport is evaluated by calculating the mass transport across Drake Passage (Passage between the tip of South America and the tip of the Antarctic Peninsula).

$\mathit{ACCtransport}=\int_{\mathit{bottom}}^{\mathit{surface}}u\, \mathit{hfac} \,dy\,dz$

  • Integrate only over the Southern Ocean (30°S-80°S)
  • Transport should be in Sv (1 Sv=10$^{6}$ m$^{3}$/s)

MOC¶

Residual MOC = Eulerian mean component + eddy component
$\overline{\Psi}$ (Resolved flow)
Given by the velocity output		 $\Psi'$ (Parameterized flow)
Given by the GM
parameterization
(gmredi package)

Eddy component

  • Variable GM_PsiY found in the Diag* files (already a streamfunction)
  • Mask the zero values in the GM_PsiY variable
  • For each year of the simulation, calculate the zonal integral of GM_PsiY

$\Psi'=\oint\mathit{GM_{PsiY}}\,dx$

Eularian mean component

  • Load the meridional velocity component VVELMASS in Diag* files
  • For each year of the simulation, calculate the cumulative vertical sum and zonal integral of VVELMASS
$$ \overline{\Psi}(t, y, z) = -\oint \int_{\mathit{bottom}}^{z} \mathit{VVELMASS}(t, y, z')\,\mathit{hfac}\,dz'\,dx $$
$\mathit{VVELMASS}:$ 1-year (annual) average
$\mathit{hfac}:$ variable hfacs
$\mathit{dz'}:$ variable drF
$\mathit{dx}:$ variable dxG
  • Give both components in Sv
  • For the cumulative sum you can use numpy.cumsum and for the simple integral numpy.sum
